posts.content:
@B7L7 Kape via owning Horiguchi (out of all jokes, I seriously think Kape wins, no bias)
Putting this as an Apex main event is diabolical. Tbh the dudes could have gone to Japan like you said and maybe delay Van Taira for there as a main event.
Kape does not deserve to fight in the Apex (3rd time in a row) neither does Horiguchi (2nd time in a row)

@grayerman it's a good idea to show just the rankings movements from the previous ranking. not sure when we can get to it but I'll put it on a tracking list we have.

@FistyMcKickerChoke we haven't been able to roll out that many user requested items lately. hopefully some day that will change. we've just been way too busy with other stuff.

@connorbrown16 we do plan to have more sports be pickable. not sure if it will happen this year. i know it's a popular request in the forums here but it's actually kind of a niche thing compared to what most people use tapology for.

@Supreme Cypher if we do make KB/MT available for picking it would not mean that we started investing more in filling out fighter KB/MT records. we would just make whatever happens to be listed pickable.

we have added a handful of editors over the years to try and focus on KB/MT but none of them have really worked out as far as pouring in a lot of updates. @D1D4K10 actually just signed up and we'll see how into it he gets. It really takes a lot of persistence to put so much data in, and we do NOT have the budget to pay anything like a full time salary for this.

@film I've spent a lot of time contemplating if we would ever allow you to pick "split" vs "unanimous" and for now the answer remains no. it's just pretty arbitrary and random of a ****** judge gets the fight scored wrong. it just feels too random and not skill-related. i am more intrigued by the idea of tagging "lock of the night" or other kinds of fun add-ons like that. but... nothing imminent.

The next feature that's actually coming out soon is an ad-free subscription option. Obviously this is not a feature like picking kickboxing that most of you are clamoring for. But we need advertising to make the site work, and the advertisements have been slowly getting more annoying. Having an ad-free option will allow you to skip all the ads entirely, but allows Tapology to still function as a business.

@Gregory
Tbh I don't think the Ad Subscription idea would work, because people can just install an adblock to their browser cost free and It doesn't display any advertisements.

* Edited at 03.25.2026,  3:24 PM ET *

@grayerman

Ben White is a funny one. Very controversial among England fans for leaving our 2022 World Cup squad due to a disagreement with the assistant manager and then refused to play for England for the rest of the time Sir Gareth Southgate was in charge. He then comes back for the first time tonight and scores what we all thought was the winner! Sure, it was a tap in, but it still needed someone's foot to be there! Then he goes and concedes a late penalty that Uruguay equalise from. An absolutely chaotic return to the team which I suppose is fitting given how controversial he is amongst England fans. The penalty he conceded was actually one of the decisions the ref got right in the game, there's no denying it was a penalty.

That's still not even the main talking point of the game! The ref didn't give a red card for a dangerous tackle on Phil Foden (or any card for that matter!) and then showed the same player 2 yellow cards but didn't send him off! It doesn't really matter too much given it was just a friendly but if England are involved in a game like that at the World Cup this summer, I can't promise I won't say something that would force @Gregory to suspend me for a bit!
